https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/tree/main
Download the Wan2_1_VACE_1_3B_preview_bf16.safetensors file and put it into ComfyUI>models>diffusion_models, then select it in the "WanVideo VACE Model Select"

The rest of the models are the same as base Wan2.1. If you do not already have Wan2.1 Setup, GO TO THIS LINK AND WATCH THE VIDEO:
https://youtu.be/D4VLXF4ZNq0?si=2c3ekxuDbKbc5m-K
A scenery video of an empty park
<- To learn how to use this click the tool tip!
DO NOT USE MASK BLURRING. VACE doesn't handle the blurring properly and you'll be left with artifacts
You can use any pre-processor you'd like, I'm using Depth here. DWPose, Canny, Lineart, all work as expected.

The flux group takes a lot of VRAM, if you are strugging with that, you can use SD15 or SDXL instead
Flux model: https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev
Flux Clips (Text Encoders): https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/tree/main
For flux, make sure to download flux union controlnet.
https://huggingface.co/Shakker-Labs/FLUX.1-dev-ControlNet-Union-Pro/tree/main

If you want to use the SDXL controlnet, just make sure to switch the "controlnet image" node
SDXL Model: https://civitai.com/models/133005/juggernaut-xl
SDXL Controlnets: https://huggingface.co/lllyasviel/sd_control_collection/tree/main

Put the controlnets in the models > controlnet folder
You can use any pre-processor you'd like, I'm using lineart here. DWPose, Canny, Lineart, all work as expected.
